        {
            "_id": "bbe167209a74dafd",
            "_key": "!journal.pages!39cca4d8a2aff3c0.bbe167209a74dafd",
            "_stats": {
                "compodiumSource": null,
                "coreVersion": "12.327",
                "createdTime": 1722088240.759506,
                "duplicateSource": null,
                "lastModifiedBy": "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y",
                "modifiedTime": 1722088240.759506,
                "systemId": "dc20rpg",
                "systemVersion": "0.8.0"
            },
            "flags": {},
            "image": {},
            "name": "Melee Attack",
            "ownership": {
                "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y": 3,
                "default": -1
            },
            "sort": 7,
            "src": null,
            "system": {},
            "text": {
                "content": "<p>When a creature makes a Melee Attack it can do so against a target within its Melee Range. A creature\u2019s Melee Range is 1 Space, unless otherwise stated (see \"Spaces & Distance\" on page 65).</p>",
                "format": 1
            },
            "title": {
                "level": 3,
                "show": true
            },
            "type": "text",
            "video": {
                "controls": true,
                "volume": 0.5
            }
        },
        {
            "_id": "b0f2519fb36f2f3a",
            "_key": "!journal.pages!39cca4d8a2aff3c0.b0f2519fb36f2f3a",
            "_stats": {
                "compodiumSource": null,
                "coreVersion": "12.327",
                "createdTime": 1722088240.759506,
                "duplicateSource": null,
                "lastModifiedBy": "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y",
                "modifiedTime": 1722088240.759506,
                "systemId": "dc20rpg",
                "systemVersion": "0.8.0"
            },
            "flags": {},
            "image": {},
            "name": "Ranged Attack",
            "ownership": {
                "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y": 3,
                "default": -1
            },
            "sort": 8,
            "src": null,
            "system": {},
            "text": {
                "content": "<p>When a creature makes a Ranged Attack it can do so against a target within its Range. The Range is determined by the type of Weapon it\u2019s Attacking with or by consulting the Feature or Spell it\u2019s using to make the Ranged Attack.</p><p><strong><em>Close Quarters</em></strong>: A creature has DisADV on Ranged Attacks while an enemy is within 1 Space of it, provided the enemy isn\u2019t Incapacitated.</p><p><strong>Weapon Ranges</strong> A Weapon that can be used to make a Ranged Attack has a Range shown in parentheses after its Ammo or Thrown property (see \u201cWeapons\u201d on page (see \"Weapons\" on page 73)).</p><p><strong><em>Normal Range:</em></strong> The first number in the parentheses is a Weapon\u2019s normal range. You can make an attack against any target within this range.</p><p><strong><em>Long Range:</em></strong> The second number in the parentheses is a Weapon\u2019s long range. You can make an attack with DisADV against targets within this range.</p><p>You can\u2019t make attacks against targets beyond your Weapon\u2019s long range.</p><div class=\"book-block book-block-example\">A Short Bow has a range of (15/45), which means that they can make Attacks against targets between 1 and 20 Spaces, can make Attacks with DisADV against targets between 21 and 60 Spaces, and they can\u2019t Attack targets that are 61 Spaces or farther away.</div>",
                "format": 1
            },
            "title": {
                "level": 3,
                "show": true
            },
            "type": "text",
            "video": {
                "controls": true,
                "volume": 0.5
            }
        },
        {
            "_id": "9ec338cb988e0c8d",
            "_key": "!journal.pages!39cca4d8a2aff3c0.9ec338cb988e0c8d",
            "_stats": {
                "compodiumSource": null,
                "coreVersion": "12.327",
                "createdTime": 1722088240.759506,
                "duplicateSource": null,
                "lastModifiedBy": "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y",
                "modifiedTime": 1722088240.759506,
                "systemId": "dc20rpg",
                "systemVersion": "0.8.0"
            },
            "flags": {},
            "image": {},
            "name": "Determining if an Attack Hits",
            "ownership": {
                "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y": 3,
                "default": -1
            },
            "sort": 9,
            "src": null,
            "system": {},
            "text": {
                "content": "<p>When a creature makes an Attack, the result of the Attack Check or Spell Check is compared to the target\u2019s Defense to determine whether or not the Attack hits the target. The Attack hits if the result of the Attack Check is equal to or greater than the target\u2019s Defense.</p><div class=\"book-block book-block-example\">A Level 4 Fighter\u2019s highest Attribute is a 3 (Prime Modifier) and their Combat Mastery is 2 (1/2 its level). When the Fighter makes an Attack Check using a Longsword, they roll a d20 and add 5 (2+3). If they roll a 10 on the d20, the result is 15 (10 + 5). If the target\u2019s Physical Defense is 15 or lower, the Attack hits, otherwise it misses.</div>",
                "format": 1
            },
            "title": {
                "level": 2,
                "show": true
            },
            "type": "text",
            "video": {
                "controls": true,
                "volume": 0.5
            }
        },
        {
            "_id": "bc1e6f55665d887f",
            "_key": "!journal.pages!39cca4d8a2aff3c0.bc1e6f55665d887f",
            "_stats": {
                "compodiumSource": null,
                "coreVersion": "12.327",
                "createdTime": 1722088240.759506,
                "duplicateSource": null,
                "lastModifiedBy": "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y",
                "modifiedTime": 1722088240.759506,
                "systemId": "dc20rpg",
                "systemVersion": "0.8.0"
            },
            "flags": {},
            "image": {},
            "name": "Defenses",
            "ownership": {
                "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y": 3,
                "default": -1
            },
            "sort": 10,
            "src": null,
            "system": {},
            "text": {
                "content": "<p>Creatures have 2 types of Defense: <strong>Physical Defense</strong> and <strong>Mystical Defense</strong>. Each type of Defense has a value that represents how difficult it is to hit a target.</p><p>When a creature makes an Attack Check or Spell Check (see \u201cAttack Checks\u201d on page 24) to attempt to deal damage to a target, the creature\u2019s Check is compared against the target\u2019s Defense to determine if the Attack hits the target.</p><div class=\"book-block book-block-dctip\">Below are the 2 different types of Defense and which damage types usually target them. There can be unique instances where a damage type targets a different defense than usual, but each ability will always say which type of Defense it targets.</div>",
                "format": 1
            },
            "title": {
                "level": 1,
                "show": true
            },
            "type": "text",
            "video": {
                "controls": true,
                "volume": 0.5
            }
        },
        {
            "_id": "d977626015393797",
            "_key": "!journal.pages!39cca4d8a2aff3c0.d977626015393797",
            "_stats": {
                "compodiumSource": null,
                "coreVersion": "12.327",
                "createdTime": 1722088240.759506,
                "duplicateSource": null,
                "lastModifiedBy": "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y",
                "modifiedTime": 1722088240.759506,
                "systemId": "dc20rpg",
                "systemVersion": "0.8.0"
            },
            "flags": {},
            "image": {},
            "name": "Physical Defense",
            "ownership": {
                "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y": 3,
                "default": -1
            },
            "sort": 11,
            "src": null,
            "system": {},
            "text": {
                "content": "<p>Physical Defense (PD) represents the difficulty of hitting a creature with physical or elemental attacks that affect the body, such as:</p><div class=\"book-block book-block-example\">Being hit by a Weapon, burnt by a Fireball, or struck by a toxic needle.</div><ul><li>Bludgeoning</li><li>Cold</li><li>Corrosion</li><li>Fire</li><li>Lightning</li><li>Piercing</li><li>Poison</li><li>Slashing</li></ul>",
                "format": 1
            },
            "title": {
                "level": 2,
                "show": true
            },
            "type": "text",
            "video": {
                "controls": true,
                "volume": 0.5
            }
        },
        {
            "_id": "dc74d334f441b272",
            "_key": "!journal.pages!39cca4d8a2aff3c0.dc74d334f441b272",
            "_stats": {
                "compodiumSource": null,
                "coreVersion": "12.327",
                "createdTime": 1722088240.759506,
                "duplicateSource": null,
                "lastModifiedBy": "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y",
                "modifiedTime": 1722088240.759506,
                "systemId": "dc20rpg",
                "systemVersion": "0.8.0"
            },
            "flags": {},
            "image": {},
            "name": "Physical Defense Formula",
            "ownership": {
                "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y": 3,
                "default": -1
            },
            "sort": 12,
            "src": null,
            "system": {},
            "text": {
                "content": "<p>A Characters Physical Defense can be determined by their Base Defense, Combat Mastery, Agility, Armor Bonus (if applicable), and if they\u2019re wielding a Shield.</p><p><strong><em>Base of 8:</em></strong> A character starts off with a base PD of 8, which is what a typical Commoner\u2019s PD would be.</p><p><strong><em>Combat Mastery:</em></strong> The character adds its Combat Mastery to account for how experienced it is at protecting itself from danger in combat. Unless a creature has Mastery in Heavy Armor, it doesn\u2019t add its Combat Mastery to its PD while wearing Heavy Armor.</p><p><strong><em>Agility Attribute:</em></strong> A character adds its Agility to its PD to account for how well it can dodge attacks.</p><p><strong><em>Armor Bonus</em></strong>: A character wearing Armor adds the Armor Bonus granted by its Armor.</p><p><strong>Physical Defense Formula</strong></p><div class=\"book-block book-block-dctip\">The Armor Bonus for Novice Armor at Level 1 is +1.8 + Combat Mastery + Agility + Armor Bonus</div><div class=\"book-block book-block-blank\">8 + Combat Mastery + Agility + Armor Bonus</div>",
                "format": 1
            },
            "title": {
                "level": 3,
                "show": true
            },
            "type": "text",
            "video": {
                "controls": true,
                "volume": 0.5
            }
        },
        {
            "_id": "320973f4aa9c8714",
            "_key": "!journal.pages!39cca4d8a2aff3c0.320973f4aa9c8714",
            "_stats": {
                "compodiumSource": null,
                "coreVersion": "12.327",
                "createdTime": 1722088240.759506,
                "duplicateSource": null,
                "lastModifiedBy": "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y",
                "modifiedTime": 1722088240.759506,
                "systemId": "dc20rpg",
                "systemVersion": "0.8.0"
            },
            "flags": {},
            "image": {},
            "name": "Shields",
            "ownership": {
                "dOcXwrUs2VunZl0y": 3,
                "default": -1
            },
            "sort": 13,
            "src": null,
            "system": {},
            "text": {
                "content": "<p>A character wearing a Shield adds the Shield Bonus granted by its Shield to any Physical Defense formula it\u2019s using.</p>",
                "format": 1
            },
            "title": {
                "level": 3,
                "show": true
            },
            "type": "text",
